CBS HIRES DEA OFFICIAL 
CBS News said Thursday it is hiring David M. Stutman, head of the Drug 
Enforcement Administration's office here, as its consultant on stories about 
drugs and crime after he retires from the DEA. Stutman, a 26-year veteran of 
law enforcement, plans to retire Feb. 28 and will start his job in news March 
1, CBS said. 
